## Service 1 — Item Service (Port 8081)

### What it does
This service manages the **product catalog**. Every product in the system is called an Item. You can create new items, view existing ones, update them, or delete them.

### Database Table

```
items table in MySQL (item_db)
┌────┬──────────────────┬───────────────────┬─────────────┬─────────────────────┐
│ id │ name             │ description       │ category    │ created_at          │
├────┼──────────────────┼───────────────────┼─────────────┼─────────────────────┤
│  1 │ Wireless Mouse   │ Ergonomic mouse   │ Electronics │ 2025-07-28 09:00:00 │
│  2 │ USB Keyboard     │ Mechanical KB     │ Electronics │ 2025-07-28 10:00:00 │
│  3 │ Office Chair     │ Comfortable chair │ Furniture   │ 2025-07-28 11:00:00 │
└────┴──────────────────┴───────────────────┴─────────────┴─────────────────────┘
```

### APIs Available

```
POST   /api/items              → Create a new item
GET    /api/items              → Get all items
GET    /api/items/1            → Get item with id 1
GET    /api/items/category/Electronics → Get all Electronics items
PUT    /api/items/1            → Update item with id 1
DELETE /api/items/1            → Delete item with id 1
```

### What you send to create an item (JSON)

```json
{
  "name": "Wireless Mouse",
  "description": "Ergonomic wireless mouse with USB receiver",
  "category": "Electronics"
}
```

### What you get back

```json
{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Item created successfully",
  "data": {
    "id": 1,
    "name": "Wireless Mouse",
    "description": "Ergonomic wireless mouse with USB receiver",
    "category": "Electronics",
    "createdAt": "2025-07-28T09:00:00"
  }
}
```

### Files Inside Item Service

```
ItemServiceApplication.java  → Main file, starts the application

model/
  Item.java                  → Represents the items table in database

dto/
  ItemDTO.java               → What data comes in and goes out
  ApiResponse.java           → Standard wrapper for all responses

repository/
  ItemRepository.java        → Talks to the database

service/
  ItemService.java           → Defines what operations exist
  ItemServiceImpl.java       → Actually does the operations

controller/
  ItemController.java        → Receives API requests

exception/
  ItemNotFoundException.java      → Custom error when item not found
  GlobalExceptionHandler.java     → Handles all errors cleanly

config/
  JwtUtil.java               → JWT token helper
  JwtAuthFilter.java         → Checks token on every request
  SecurityConfig.java        → Security rules
  OpenApiConfig.java         → Swagger setup
```

