## Service 2 — Inventory Service (Port 8082)

### What it does
This service tracks **how many units of each item are available** in the warehouse. When you add stock, update quantity, or check how many items are left, this service handles it. It also has a special feature to find items that are running low on stock.

### Database Table

```
inventory table in MySQL (inventory_db)
┌────┬─────────┬──────────┬────────────────────┬─────────────────────┐
│ id │ item_id │ quantity │ warehouse_location  │ last_updated        │
├────┼─────────┼──────────┼────────────────────┼─────────────────────┤
│  1 │    1    │   150    │ A1-North            │ 2025-07-28 10:30:00 │
│  2 │    2    │    45    │ B2-South            │ 2025-07-28 11:00:00 │
│  3 │    3    │     8    │ C1-East             │ 2025-07-28 11:30:00 │
└────┴─────────┴──────────┴────────────────────┴─────────────────────┘
```

Notice item_id connects to the items table. Item with id=1 (Wireless Mouse) has 150 units in warehouse A1-North.

### APIs Available

```
POST   /api/inventory                    → Add inventory for an item
GET    /api/inventory                    → Get all inventory records
GET    /api/inventory/1                  → Get inventory record by id
GET    /api/inventory/item/1             → Get inventory for item id 1
GET    /api/inventory/low-stock?threshold=10 → Items with less than 10 units
PUT    /api/inventory/1                  → Update inventory record
DELETE /api/inventory/1                  → Delete inventory record
```

### What you send to add inventory (JSON)

```json
{
  "itemId": 1,
  "quantity": 150,
  "warehouseLocation": "A1-North"
}
```

### What you get back

```json
{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Inventory added successfully",
  "data": {
    "id": 1,
    "itemId": 1,
    "quantity": 150,
    "warehouseLocation": "A1-North",
    "lastUpdated": "2025-07-28T10:30:00"
  }
}
```

### Special Feature — Low Stock

```
GET /api/inventory/low-stock?threshold=10
```

This returns all items that have quantity less than 10 units. Very useful for the warehouse manager to know when to reorder stock.

```json
{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Low stock items retrieved",
  "data": [
    {
      "id": 3,
      "itemId": 3,
      "quantity": 8,
      "warehouseLocation": "C1-East"
    }
  ]
}
```

