## Service 4 — Audit Service (Port 8084)

### What it does
This service is like a **diary of the entire system**. Every important action that happens — creating an item, deleting inventory, sending a notification — gets recorded here. This is important for security, compliance, and debugging. If something goes wrong, you can look at the audit log and see exactly what happened and when.

### Database Table

```
audit_logs table in MySQL (audit_db)
┌────┬──────────────────┬───────────┬───────────┬─────────────────────┬──────────────────────────┐
│ id │ service_name     │ operation │ record_id │ timestamp           │ details                  │
├────┼──────────────────┼───────────┼───────────┼─────────────────────┼──────────────────────────┤
│  1 │ Item Service     │ CREATE    │   1       │ 2025-07-28 09:00:00 │ Item created by admin    │
│  2 │ Inventory Service│ UPDATE    │   1       │ 2025-07-28 10:30:00 │ Quantity updated to 150  │
│  3 │ Item Service     │ DELETE    │   5       │ 2025-07-28 12:00:00 │ Item deleted by admin    │
└────┴──────────────────┴───────────┴───────────┴─────────────────────┴──────────────────────────┘
```

### APIs Available

```
POST   /api/audit-logs                      → Log a new event
GET    /api/audit-logs                      → Get all audit logs
GET    /api/audit-logs/1                    → Get log by id
GET    /api/audit-logs/service/Item Service → Logs by service name
GET    /api/audit-logs/operation/DELETE     → All DELETE operations
GET    /api/audit-logs/record/1             → All logs for record id 1
PUT    /api/audit-logs/1                    → Update a log
DELETE /api/audit-logs/1                    → Delete a log
```

### What you send to log an event (JSON)

```json
{
  "serviceName": "Item Service",
  "operation": "DELETE",
  "recordId": 1005,
  "details": "Item deleted by admin user"
}
```

### What you get back

```json
{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Audit log created successfully",
  "data": {
    "id": 1,
    "serviceName": "Item Service",
    "operation": "DELETE",
    "recordId": 1005,
    "timestamp": "2025-07-28T12:00:00",
    "details": "Item deleted by admin user"
  }
}
```

